                  </hi>. (<hi rend="italic">Policeman</hi>). I produce a certificate—(<hi rend="italic">
This certified the Conviction of James Nubley, at Clerkenwell, in Nov., 1851, of larceny, and that he was sentenced to six months imprisonment</hi>)—Mackness is the person who was convicted in that name.</p>
